 ('2', '37', 'en_ca', 'Gamma Irradiation', 'gamma', '(Not final) Konnexis has developed a system for Gamma and E-Beam irradiators that is highly flexible in order to both suit your needs and to accommodate for the changing industry. Through seamless integration between irradiator control and product tracking, Konnexis has allowed its Gamma irradiation customers to reach unparalleled levels of productivity.', '2015-10-17 15:24:18', '2015-12-30 17:03:14', 'a97f5ba7-4239-4da6-84ae-50736fc937f1'),
 ('3', '38', 'en_ca', 'Electron Beam (E-Beam)', 'ebeam', '(Not final) Konnexis has developed a system for Gamma and E-Beam irradiators that is highly flexible in order to both suit your needs and to accommodate for the changing industry. Through seamless integration between irradiator control and product tracking, Konnexis has allowed its Gamma irradiation customers to reach unparalleled levels of productivity.', '2015-10-17 15:24:18', '2015-12-30 17:03:14', 'c91afac6-19b7-4ed3-8029-8e81e5d36bfa'),
 ('4', '39', 'en_ca', 'X-Ray', 'xray', '(Not final) Konnexis\' innovation in X-Ray sterilization has accelerated the industry and allowed the technology to advance to new heights. Through seamless integration between irradiator control and product tracking, Konnexis allows you effortless processing and reliability.', '2015-10-17 15:24:18', '2015-12-30 17:03:14', '07c0975a-d36c-4f69-b6a4-0ace11ac730e'),
 ('5', '59', 'en_ca', 'Ethylene Oxide', 'oxide', 'Ethylene oxide (EtO) sterilization uses EtO gas to sterilize equipment that requires lower temperatures. It is widely used across the sterilization industry for its proven methods as well as its universal compatibility: most products can be sterilized using ethylene oxide gas, including devices that contain plastic or electronic components. EtO infiltrates packaging, allowing it to sterilize organisms on a product from manufacturing and packaging processes. As sterilizers have been using EtO sterilization since the 1950s, there is a lot of information on this method. It is reliable, requires low capital investment, and most sterilizers know exactly what they are getting into when they use it. However, there are also disadvantages to using EtO gas. It is a fairly complex process, and requires longer product holdup for airing. Because of its complexity, as well as its explosive quality, a proven and detailed control system is essential.  There are three phases to sterilizing with ethylene oxide. First is pre-conditioning, where a batch is prepared for sterilizers using humidity so organisms grow. Once this is done, the batch is moved to the sterilization phase. The sterilization phase is long and complex; and must be closely monitored for accuracy and safety. Our software creates ease-of-access and use for process monitoring while creating detailed reports for documentation and auto-batch release. After sterilization is complete, a batch must be degassed in a temperature-controlled environment. This removes any EtO from the product, insuring safety, before batches are shipped for use.', '2015-12-29 19:02:15', '2015-12-29 19:08:44', 'df31c169-3026-463f-84e2-027251747f0c'),
 ('6', '60', 'en_ca', 'Gamma', 'gamma', 'This content needs to be added', '2015-12-29 19:08:44', '2015-12-29 19:08:44', '581d2a72-80b5-47fa-89fc-f12a5d1835f4'),
